This message is for the parents and students of the Mount Union Area School District.

The Mount Union Area School District will welcome students back to school on Wednesday August 26, 2020. We will be returning face-to-face with all students, understanding some students have chosen our remote option. Students and staff are reminded to wear a comfortable face covering as mandated by the Pennsylvania Department of Health. Those parents who selected the remote option for your students are asked to complete the Remote Learning form on our website. We look forward to welcoming your child back to school!

If you do not plan to utilize district transportation and plan to transport your student to and from school for the 2020-2021 school year, please complete the transportation opt out form link located on the school district website at www.muasd.org no later than Monday, August 24, 2020 by 3:00 PM. post_text:
Please reference the MUASD website for the following:

MUASD 2020-2021 Remote Learning Form

This form should only be completed by parents who have elected to enroll their child in remote learning for the 2020-2021 school year. Please understand that all students participating in remote instruction will need to have access to internet service as your child will need to log on and participate in their classes live each day. Students will be responsible for completing all the same assignments with the same due date as students participating in person. Assignments will be submitted online unless special arrangements are made with the teacher. It is important to understand that students must maintain their attendance and grades.

Please complete this form for each child that will be participating in remote learning by Monday, August 24, 2020.

post_text:
Mount Union Area High School Senior, Christian Queen...

Christian you have came a long way. Your birth year was hectic and now your graduation year is crazy. You have developed into a loving, caring, thoughtful young man. Your outlook on life is amazing. You have brought us so much joy and happiness throughout the years. In all this madness going on, you have not lost focus on your future. We are proud to have you for your accomplishments. Always aim for the sky in your endeavors. You create your own path to success. As you are always told, make it happen. We will always cherish the good and bad times together, they have definitely made you a better person. We love you and wish you the best. Class of 2020.

Love,
Dad, Angel, Justin, Nana, Pappy and Gram.

shared_text:
Erica Miller Dell shared a post to the group: Mapleton-Union Elementary CTO.
April 24 at 3:57 PM ¬∑

Music at Mount Union
April 24 at 9:50 AM ¬∑

April and May are normally crazy busy months in the music department. Days are filled with tons music! Students are busy performing at concerts, graduations, parades, and so much more! COVID has silenced much of those big ensembles this year. To give our students some room to shine, we would like to feature our MU musicians!
If you have a child that participates in band and/or chorus we would love to showcase them!!! Please MESSAGE us their picture (maybe even with their instrument) and then their bio. We would love for the bio to include: Name, Grade, Instrument/Voice, why they joined band/chorus, why they have stayed in band/chorus, why they love it, what music means to them, what they are looking forward to when band/chorus resumes in school.
We can't wait to showcase all the cool musicians at MU!!
And remember do something musical EVERY day!! #dosomethingmusicaleveryday

Mount Union Area High School Senior, Sydney Dimoff...

My sweet Syd,

I want you to know how proud I am of the young woman you've become. You are always positive, wanting to help others and always smiling!! You stay busy going to school, working as many hours as you can at Giant, being a great big sister to Maddie and helping me with housework. I admire your work ethic! I know how excited you were for this, your Senior year, to finally be here...and I know how very sad you are for it have to end like this. It breaks my heart to see you so upset. Just know, good things are to come! You are going to start a new chapter in your life this fall at Shippensburg University! I'm so excited for you!!! I know you will do well, just keep that beautiful smile going!!! I Love You ‚ù§

Love,
Dad

Mount Union Area High School Senior, Justin Chaney...

Jac, we are so very proud of you and all that you have accomplished through your elementary and high school education. It‚Äôs hard to believe that the time is already here to say goodbye and to move on to college in the fall. I can‚Äôt wait to see what the future holds for you wherever you decide to go, whether it‚Äôs Penn State or Pitt... Science is a good choice for you and will lead to a great future I have no doubt. You are such a great person and an awesome son and big brother. I am so sad that this year is not what it‚Äôs supposed to be and I hope that you have no regrets about your senior year. We will always be in your corner no matter what life throws at you and what your future may bring. May God guide you through all the tough decisions that you will have to make. Follow your dreams!

Love, Mom, Dad, Allyssa and Jerrick

post_text:
Mount Union Area High School Senior, Derek Williams...

Derek,
What a journey this has been, it all started the day you were born. Sometimes, it has felt like a roller coaster. You always fight your way thru no matter the obstacle that comes your way, when you play soccer, for example, you might fall down (a lot), but you always jump back up and go even harder toward the goal. During school, extracurricular activities, and community service, you always give it your all. Your strong will is going to let you succeed in whatever you set your mind towards. Life is going to have detours, and even some, misdirection. Trust in God and remember we will always be here for you. We can't wait to see where this ride goes next through your journey at Juniata College.

Love you always,
Dad, Mom, and Chelsea
P.s. Tie your shoes

post_text:
Mount Union Area High School Senior, Timothy Andrews...

Timothy has a heart of gold and has always put his family and friends first beyond anything. He is the third oldest in a household of six children and looks out for his younger siblings in so many ways. He have been a role model to them (although pillow fights in the living room should never happen üòä). Although he may not tell them he does truly care and love them. His goal is to be able to go into the Navy and he has been working hard to meet the standards the Navy has. He is almost there and we are beyond proud of him for wanting to follow in the family tradition of the military.

Timothy, we know your senior year is not going as expected and this has been yet another challenge that we know you will be able to overcome. You have a zest for life and such a caring heart, we know this will just make you stronger and more determined for your future aspirations of enlisting in the U.S. Navy. You have made us proud and continue to do so. Love you always, Todd, Mom, Levi, Eion, Emma, Cassandra, and Mason.

post_text:
Mount Union Area High School Senior, Destinie Myers...

Meet Destinie Myers, better known as Des. During her years at Mount Union she has been a volleyball and softball player and also a member of National Honor Society as well as a Champ Captain in 2020. Des has committed to attend Coastal Carolina University after graduation to study political science with hopes of continuing on to law school. With her ability to argue, I believe this could be the perfect career for her. J Des has an amazing group of friends she has spent most of her years of high school with and I hope that when she looks back on her days at MU she remembers the good times and group get togethers. This is a tough time for all of the kids in the senior class and I wish for them to hold tight to the memories they have and look forward to the new adventures ahead.

Des- I wish you the best in your future and want you to know how very proud I am of you.

Love,
Mom

Dear Mount Union Community Parents/Guardians and Teachers....

Let‚Äôs come together to celebrate our seniors. If you would like to have your senior student highlighted on our District‚Äôs FB page, please send their photo and a brief write-up that captures who they are as a person, student, son or daughter.

Our kids have done and will continue to do great things...We are hoping this will be one way to let them know they are special, cared for, and not forgotten during this difficult time.

Please send senior photos and write ups to either Dr. Dianne Thomas (dthomas@muasd.org) or Mrs. Maurine Hockenberry (mhockenberry@muasd.org). We are looking forward to sharing this information.

Stay safe and well.

post_text:
School Closure Update

Mount Union Area School District students will return to school on Thursday, April 9th (snow make-up day). Staff will return on Tuesday, April 7th. There will be no school on Friday, April 10th. Due to the extended closure we will be utilizing the remaining designated snow days on the school calendar. Students will be in session on Monday, April 13th.

The Department of Education (PDE) announced today all schools in the commonwealth will remain closed through at least April 6th as a result of the COVID-19 response efforts. The closure order could be extended beyond April 6th if necessary to save lives and stop the spread of COVID-19.

Under the new timeline, school buildings would reopen on April 7th for two days to allow school administrators, teachers and other staff time to prepare classrooms, set up cafeterias, schedule transportation and arrange other business operations. Students would return to school on April 9th, unless extending the closure is needed in response to the situation with the virus at that time.

post_text:
Free Lunch Program

The Mount Union Area School District will be offering free lunches to anyone age 18 or under beginning on Monday, March 30th and continuing until students return to school. Lunches will be distributed at each of our school buildings (Kistler Elementary, Shirley Township Elementary, Mapleton Elementary, and the Junior/Senior High School) Monday through Friday from 11:30 AM until 12:30 PM. The process will be Grab-n-Go curbside, anyone age 18 or under in the vehicle or in person will receive a free lunch. The distribution area for the Junior/Senior High School will be located in the back parking lot near the baseball field.
